!!!LVM needs activation
sudo vgscan && sudo vgchange -ay    (activation)
sudo vgs && sudo lvs     (See group and logical volume)
lsblk -f    (Check FS type)

!!!How to deal with USB with file.iso type on partition
Make sure disk is unmount (May have to change config using Disks GUI)
format the disk fat32   (Use GUI or term)
wipefs -a: Removes all known filesystems and partition table signatures.
dd if=/dev/zero: Overwrites the beginning of the drive (100MB is usually enough to kill any boot records or persistent config).
Wipe existing partition table clean:
sudo wipefs -a /dev/sdX
sudo dd if=/dev/zero of=/dev/sdX bs=1M status=progress count=100

OR
mount the partition then
cd /run/media/aruffin/Ventoy   (the path where *.iso exist)
rm -rf ./*

This replaces the existing partition table with a blank GPT table — fast and safe.
Wipe Only Partition Table
sudo parted /dev/sdX mklabel gpt

If you want to reuse the USB stick:  
sudo parted /dev/sdX mklabel gpt
sudo parted -a opt /dev/sdX mkpart primary fat32 1MiB 100%
sudo mkfs.vfat -F32 /dev/sdX1

how do I LVM filesystem's partition type.
Confirm the logical volume device path
sudo lvdisplay   (Look for path: /dev/vg_external/lv_tmp)

Unmount the filesystem (if mounted): Check if it’s mounted:
mount | grep lv_tmp

If it is, unmount it:
sudo umount /dev/vg_external/lv_tmp

!!!Correct Way to Set Up Swap on LVM
sudo mkswap /dev/vg_external/lv_swap
sudo swapon /dev/vg_external/lv_swap      (Initialize it)

Remove the existing filesystem
sudo wipefs -a /dev/vg_external/lv_tmp   (Wipe FS type only not size)

Create the new filesystem
sudo mkfs.xfs /dev/vg_external/lv_tmp

lvresize:to resize an existing LV | lvremove:to delete an LV.| lvcreate to make a new one.
sudo lvresize -L 4G /dev/vg_external/lv_tmp

mount it back:
sudo mount /dev/vg_external/lv_tmp

How to Add a Directory to $PATH
Temporarily (for current shell session only)
export PATH=$PATH:/new/directory/path
Example: export PATH=$PATH:/home/axruffin/scripts

Permanently (survives reboot / new terminal sessions)
nano ~/.bashrc
export PATH=$PATH:/home/axruffin/scripts
source ~/.bashrc

Get info on partition such as sector(Start,end), size, name, flags
sudo parted /dev/nvme0n1 print

Find the device
sudo fdisk -l

See logical volumes
lsblk -f

see if the kernel detected
dmesg --follow
dmesg | grep -i sd
dmesg | tail -n 50

Create a mount point
sudo mkdir /mnt/mydrive

Mount the filesystem
sudo mount -t ext4 /dev/sdb1 /mnt/mydrive

Unmount when done
sudo umount /mnt/mydrive

View mounted filesystems
df -ha

Confirm drive is visible at USB level
lsusb

[ -d /sys/firmware/efi ] && echo "UEFI boot" || echo "Legacy BIOS boot"

